(44, 19, 3, 40, 28, 19, 19, 'Unto John’s baptism', 'Baptism and Its Significance', 'This connection highlights the theme of baptism in both passages. Acts 19:3 refers to John''s baptism, while Matthew 28:19 emphasizes the command to baptize in the name of the Father, Son, and Holy Ghost.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 3, 42, 3, 1, 38, 'Unto John’s baptism', 'Baptism of Repentance Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of baptism as a significant act of repentance. Both passages reference baptism, with Acts mentioning ''John''s baptism'' and Luke detailing John''s ministry of baptism for the remission of sins.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 3, 44, 8, 16, 16, 'Unto John’s baptism', 'Baptism in Early Church', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of baptism, specifically referencing different forms of baptism. Acts 19:3 mentions John''s baptism, while Acts 8:16 refers to baptism in the name of the Lord Jesus, highlighting the transition in the understanding of baptism within the early church.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 3, 46, 12, 13, 13, 'Unto what then were ye baptized', 'Baptism and Unity in Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of baptism as a significant act of initiation into the community of believers. Both passages emphasize the transformative nature of baptism, with Acts referencing John''s baptism and 1 Corinthians discussing baptism into one body by the Spirit.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 4, 43, 1, 29, 34, 'that they should believe on him', 'Baptism and Belief Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of baptism as a precursor to belief in Christ. Both passages emphasize the role of John the Baptist in preparing the way for Jesus, specifically mentioning belief in him.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
